metadata.content:
# Unidentified pirate shanty - Behind the scenes[]

The pirate shanty debuted in "Zero Friends Again," the sixth episode of the live-action television series Star Wars: Skeleton Crew, aired on December 31, 2024. The song's division into verses and stanzas, in turn, was specified in the subtitles prepared by Disney+.

As revealed by "Zero Friends Again" director Bryce Dallas Howard, the pirate shanty was supposed to be a poem before Silvo's actor Jude Law suggested that he could sing it. According to Law, shanties were a characteristic feature of pirate lore. Howard and other series creators took keenly to Law's proposition. In this way, the poem made its way to the episode in a musical form.
metadata.title: Unidentified pirate shanty

# Unidentified song (Aqualish)

An Aqualish played a song on the moon Pantora while he was in his hovertruck. Since the Aqualish was listening to the music, he was oblivious to the fact that the clone Omega had just pulled a lever on the hovertruck, causing all of the crates that were strapped on to the hovertruck to fall onto the ground. He was also unaware of the fact that the bounty hunter Fennec Shand and Omega had been fighting on top of his hovertruck.
metadata.title: Unidentified song (Aqualish)

# Unidentified singer

A female singer was once captured by the pirate Bar-Kooda and brought aboard his starship, the Bloodstar. She sang a song about a binggy to Bar-Kooda and his crew of pirates. Despite being saddened by the song, Bar-Kooda shot the singer, noting that the pirates would be able to make a fine supper out of her.
